growth_protocol_ch1: Fresh-frozen human prefrontal cortex tissue (25-50 mg) was lysed and homogenized in 1 mL TRIzol (Invitrogen) in Precellys Lysing Kit CKMix tubes using a MiniLys homogenizer (Bertin Instruments, two intervals of 10 s on the highest setting with 15 s in between). Homogenate was immediately placed on ice and transferred to DNA LoBind Tubes (Eppendorf)
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was isolated using the standard TRIzol protocol and re-suspended in 85 uL Ultrapure Distilled water (Invitrogen). DNase treatment was performed in solution with the RNase-Free DNase Set (Qiagen) using 5 uL DNase I and 10 uL RDD buffer, followed by a column cleanup using the RNeasy Mini Kit (Qiagen) with two additional washes (75% ethanol) before elution
extract_protocol_ch1.1: Libraries were prepared by the Van Andel Genomics Core from 500 ng of total RNA using the KAPA RNA HyperPrep Kit with RiboseErase (v1.16) (Kapa Biosystems). RNA was sheared to an average of 300 bp. Prior to PCR amplification, cDNA fragments were ligated to Bioo Scientific NEXTflex Adapters (Bioo Scientific). Quality and quantity of the finished libraries were assessed using a combination of Agilent DNA High Sensitivity chip (Agilent Technologies Inc.) and QuantiFluor® dsDNA System (Promega Corp.). Individually indexed libraries were pooled and 75 bp, single end sequencing was performed on an Illumina NextSeq 500 sequencer using a 75 bp HO sequencing kit (v2) (Illumina Inc.), with all libraries run across 4 flowcells to return a minimum read depth of 40M read pairs per library.  Base calling was done by Illumina NextSeq Control Software (NCS) v2.0 and output of NCS was demultiplexed and converted to FastQ format with Illumina Bcl2fastq v1.9.0.
data_processing: Trim Galore was used to trim the 75bp single-end reads prior to genome alignment
data_processing.1: STAR index was generated using Ensemble GRCh37.p13 primary assembly genome and the Gencode v19 primary assembly annotation
data_processing.2: Read alignment and gene counts were performed using STAR
data_processing.3: Gene count matrix was imported into R (v3.4.1) and low expressed genes (counts per million < 1 in more than 30% of samples) were removed prior to trimmed mean of M-values normalization in EdgeR
data_processing.4: The limma statistical package19 was used to transform the count matrix to log2-counts per million and fit a robust linear model
data_processing.6: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: Each ReadsPerGene.out.tab file contain the following information in order: gene ID, counts for unstranded RNA-seq, counts for the 1st read strand aligned with RNA, counts for the 2nd read strand aligned with RNA

Homogenate was immediately placed on ice and transferred to DNA LoBind Tubes (Eppendorf)
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was isolated using the standard TRIzol protocol and re-suspended in 85 uL Ultrapure Distilled water (Invitrogen). DNase treatment was performed in solution with the RNase-Free DNase Set (Qiagen) using 5 uL DNase I and 10 uL RDD buffer, followed by a column cleanup using the RNeasy Mini Kit (Qiagen) with two additional washes (75% ethanol) before elution
extract_protocol_ch1.1: Libraries were prepared by the Van Andel Genomics Core from 500 ng of total RNA using the KAPA RNA HyperPrep Kit with RiboseErase (v1.16) (Kapa Biosystems). RNA was sheared to an average of 300 bp. Prior to PCR amplification, cDNA fragments were ligated to Bioo Scientific NEXTflex Adapters (Bioo Scientific). Quality and quantity of the finished libraries were assessed using a combination of Agilent DNA High Sensitivity chip (Agilent Technologies Inc.) and QuantiFluor® dsDNA System (Promega Corp.). Individually indexed libraries were pooled and 75 bp, single end sequencing was performed on an Illumina NextSeq 500 sequencer using a 75 bp HO sequencing kit (v2) (Illumina Inc.), with all libraries run across 4 flowcells to return a minimum read depth of 40M read pairs per library.  Base calling was done by Illumina NextSeq Control Software (NCS) v2.0 and output of NCS was demultiplexed and converted to FastQ format with Illumina Bcl2fastq v1.9.0.
data_processing: Trim Galore was used to trim the 75bp single-end reads prior to genome alignment
data_processing.1: STAR index was generated using Ensemble GRCh37.p13 primary assembly genome and the Gencode v19 primary assembly annotation
data_processing.2: Read alignment and gene counts were performed using STAR
data_processing.3: Gene count matrix was imported into R (v3.4.1) and low expressed genes (counts per million < 1 in more than 30% of samples) were removed prior to trimmed mean of M-values normalization in EdgeR
data_processing.4: The limma statistical package19 was used to transform the count matrix to log2-counts per million and fit a robust linear model

growth_protocol_ch1: Fresh-frozen human prefrontal cortex tissue (25-50 mg) was lysed and homogenized in 1 mL TRIzol (Invitrogen) in Precellys Lysing Kit CKMix tubes using a MiniLys homogenizer (Bertin Instruments, two intervals of 10 s on the highest setting with 15 s in between). extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was isolated using the standard TRIzol protocol and re-suspended in 85 uL Ultrapure Distilled water (Invitrogen). DNase treatment was performed in solution with the RNase-Free DNase Set (Qiagen) using 5 uL DNase I and 10 uL RDD buffer, followed by a column cleanup using the RNeasy Mini Kit (Qiagen) with two additional washes (75% ethanol) before elution
extract_protocol_ch1.1: Libraries were prepared by the Van Andel Genomics Core from 500 ng of total RNA using the KAPA RNA HyperPrep Kit with RiboseErase (v1.16) (Kapa Biosystems). RNA was sheared to an average of 300 bp. Prior to PCR amplification, cDNA fragments were ligated to Bioo Scientific NEXTflex Adapters (Bioo Scientific). Quality and quantity of the finished libraries were assessed using a combination of Agilent DNA High Sensitivity chip (Agilent Technologies Inc.) and QuantiFluor® dsDNA System (Promega Corp.). Individually indexed libraries were pooled and 75 bp, single end sequencing was performed on an Illumina NextSeq 500 sequencer using a 75 bp HO sequencing kit (v2) (Illumina Inc.), with all libraries run across 4 flowcells to return a minimum read depth of 40M read pairs per library.  Base calling was done by Illumina NextSeq Control Software (NCS) v2.0 and output of NCS was demultiplexed and converted to FastQ format with Illumina Bcl2fastq v1.9.0.

data_processing.4: The limma statistical package19 was used to transform the count matrix to log2-counts per million and fit a robust linear model
data_processing.6: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: Each ReadsPerGene.out.tab file contain the following information in order: gene ID, counts for unstranded RNA-seq, counts for the 1st read strand aligned with RNA, counts for the 2nd read strand aligned with RNA
